<title>USA: Informix says lays off 100 workers.</title>
<headline>Informix says lays off 100 workers.</headline>
<dateline>MENLO PARK, Calif. 1997-05-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Informix Corp laid off 100 workers yesterday as part of its plan to return to profits by the end of the year, a company spokesman said Thursday.</p>
<p>The database software company cut administrative works and technical documentation staff at its facilities in the San Francisco area and in Lenexa, Kansas, said spokesman Robert Manetta.</p>
<p>Manetta could not immediately say how much the lay offs will costs the company in charges.</p>
